      "content": "The candles have all guttered out, leaving only the cold, grey ash of what once was a life. To be betrayed so utterly... it is as if the very stars have conspired to mock my existence. I feel nothing now but a hollow, aching silence where my heart once beat. It would be so much quieter, wouldn't it? To simply step into the shadows and let the night reclaim what it lent me. There is a certain... tragic grace in the thought of finally fading away.",
